    "description": "Moon Dancer is a vertically scrolling shmup featuring an exhilarating lock-on laser. The user controls the fighter &quot;Moon Dancer&quot; equipped with shots and lock-on lasers to defeat the enemy.<br><br><strong>Game features:</strong><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>Pop and cool lock-on laser Shmup.<br></li><li> Use the NES color palette as an art style.<br></li><li> There is an &quot;arcade mode&quot; consisting of all 8 stages and a &quot;caravan mode&quot; in which you compete for a 3-minute score.<br></li><li> Supports online ranking.</li></ul><br>Arcade mode consists of eight stages. You can choose from three levels of difficulty. If you break through all the stages, the game will be cleared. <br>Caravan mode is a 3-minute limited challenge to get a high score.<br>In all modes, Local ranking and online ranking are supported.<br><br>This game requires you to quickly defeat the enemies that appear one after another.<br>The feature of this game is the balance that prioritizes attacking the enemy rather than avoiding bullets.<br><br>Two types of music are included: the original version by HIROKKEY and the chiptune arrangement version using the NES sound source by Taku Shiiba. Music can be switched in the option menu.",
